Abbey Connect — Belmont Abbey College
A student web portal for Belmont Abbey College. Built for my Web Development final project.
Live Site: https://gav-cybersec.github.io/campus-life-app/
Repository: https://github.com/gav-cybersec/campus-life-app

What It Does

Home — Hero slideshow with campus news and quick links to Events, Dining, and the Map
Events — Browse campus events filtered by Past, Today, or Upcoming
Dining — View daily menus for Maurus Hall and Holy Grounds Café, plus dining hours
Map — Campus map with key building locations and descriptions


Technologies Used

HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript
Google Fonts (DM Serif Display + DM Sans)
CSS Grid and Flexbox for layout
GitHub Pages for deployment


How to Run It

Download or clone the repo
Make sure the folder structure looks like this:

abbey-connect/
├── index.html
├── events.html
├── dining.html
├── map.html
├── css/
│   └── style.css
└── js/
    └── script.js

Open index.html in a browser — no installs needed


Features

Sticky navbar with glassmorphism blur effect and the official BAC logo
Auto-advancing hero slideshow with manual dot navigation
JavaScript tab filtering on the Events and Dining pages
Fully responsive layout that works on desktop, tablet, and mobile
Semantic HTML throughout for accessibility
All images have alt text and color contrast meets WCAG AA standards


Future Improvements

Connect dining menus to a live API so they update automatically
Add a real search feature that filters events and locations
Build an interactive campus map using Google Maps
Add a mobile hamburger menu for easier navigation on small screens